Bill Turnbull has tragically died following a five-year battle with rostate cancer, his family confirmed today, at the age of 66. A statement from his family said: "Following a challenging and committed fight against prostate cancer, Bill passed away peacefully at his home in Suffolk surrounded by his family on Wednesday, 31st August." Here, we look back at some of Bill's most memorable moments which saw him capture the hearts of the nation. From appearing on the third series of Strictly Come Dancing to starring on a Children In Need edition of Top Gear in 2012, to saying goodbye to the BBC studios in 2016, we look back at the presenter's best moments. 